properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 9 at 8:38AM CST until January 9 at 6:00PM CST by NWS La Crosse WI
properties.description:
...Slick Travel With a Light Wintry Mix Today...

.A light wintry mix, including freezing rain, is occurring across
portions of southeast Minnesota, northeast Iowa, and western
Wisconsin this morning. Untreated roads and sidewalks will become
slick with a light glazing of ice. If you have travel planned
today, slow down and be prepared for slippery conditions.

* WHAT...Mixed precipitation. Additional snow accumulations of
up to one inch and ice accumulations of up to one tenth of an
inch.

* WHERE...Taylor County.

* WHEN...Until 6 PM CST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Any untreated sidewalks, roads and bridges will become
slippery. The hazardous conditions could impact travel into this
evening.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM CST THIS EVENING
